.SH NAME
HTMLElement.hidePopover \- HTMLElement: hidePopover() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]hidePopover()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R] interface hides a popover element (i.e., one that
has a valid \f[CR]popover\f[R] attribute) by removing it from the top
layer and styling it with \f[CR]display: none\f[R].
.PP
When \f[CR]hidePopover()\f[R] is called on a showing element with the
\f[CR]popover\f[R] attribute, a \f[CR]beforetoggle\f[R] event will be
fired, followed by the popover being hidden, and then the
\f[CR]toggle\f[R] event firing.
If the element is already hidden, an error is thrown.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
hidePopover()
.EE
.SS Parameters
None.
.SS Return value
None (\f[CR]undefined\f[R]).
.SS Exceptions
.TP
\f[B]InvalidStateError\f[R] \f[B]DOMException\f[R]
Thrown if the popover is already hidden.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Hiding a popover
The following example provides functionality to hide a popover by
pressing a particular key on the keyboard.
.SS HTML
.IP
.EX
<\f[B]button\f[R] popovertarget=\(dqmypopover\(dq>Toggle popover\(aqs display</\f[B]button\f[R]>
<\f[B]div\f[R] id=\(dqmypopover\(dq popover=\(dqmanual\(dq>
  You can press <\f[B]kbd\f[R]>h</\f[B]kbd\f[R]> on your keyboard to close the popover.
</\f[B]div\f[R]>
.EE
.SS JavaScript
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] popover = document.getElementById(\(dqmypopover\(dq);

document.addEventListener(\(dqkeydown\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  \f[B]if\f[R] (event.key === \(dqh\(dq) {
    popover.hidePopover();
  }
});
.EE
